{
  "text": "On analysis of The Cancer Genome Atlas (TCGA) OVCA and normal tissue RNA sequencing data (http://gepia.cancer-pku.cn/index.html) [CITATION_1] , the expression level of DR6 was higher in OVCA than in normal tissues (Fig. 1A) . We subsequently analyzed the expression level of DR6 in OVCA cells by western blot analysis. As shown in Fig. 1B , compared with normal human ovarian surface epithelial (HOSE) cells, DR6 was significantly upregulated in the four OVCA cell lines (SKOV3, HO-8910, A2780, and OVCAR3). Total RNA and protein were isolated from OVCA tissues and from matched adjacent normal tissues to detect the expression level of DR6. The expression of DR6 was analyzed by quantitative PCR and western blot. The results indicated that the mRNA and protein expression levels of DR6 were higher in OVCA samples than they were in the matched adjacent normal samples (Fig. 1C,D) . ",
